observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management undertake the following measures:

a. Prepare and maintain stock and property cards for every type of inventories and PPEs for proper monitoring;

b. Perform periodic reconciliation of book records and inventory cards to ensure that financial discrepancies are immediately investigated, cleared and reconciled with the books of accounts;

c. Instruct the Inventory Committee to exert more effort to complete the conduct of physical inventory of all Inventory and PPE accounts and submit the Report of Physical Count of Inventory and PPE not later than January 31 each year pursuant to Government Accounting Manual for LGUs;

d. Establish the accountability for all types of PPE to heighten the security that the assets are properly safeguarded against wastage and loss;

e. Prepare necessary journal entries to adjust the duly investigated reconciling items supported with sufficient and appropriate documents in order to reflect the correct account balances;

f. Instruct the Office of the Municipal Accountant to continue its effort to locate pertinent source documents to reduce the unidentified balances in the property ledger cards, if any, in order to render a reliable and accurate financial report.

We recommended that the Management:

a. Post the reports on the receipt and utilization of DRRMF sourced from GAA and donations in the LGU-Website;

b. Instruct GSO Officer to coordinate with other offices in regards to the donated items for the maintenance of an inventory list thereof;

c. Prepare the Summary/List of Donations Received, Distributed and Balances together with the required supporting documents and submit the same promptly to COA; and

d. Adhere strictly to COA Circular No. 2014-002 and COA Circular No. 2020-009 on the accounting and reporting guidelines on the receipt and utilization of Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund, cash and in-kind donations.

4.7	We recommended that the Management undertake the following measures:
Perform periodic reconciliation of stock/property cards to ensure that discrepancies are immediately investigated, cleared and reconciled with the books of accounts;
Instruct the Inventory Committee to exert more effort to complete the conduct of physical inventory of all Inventory and PPE accounts;
Establish the accountability for all types of PPE to heighten the security that the assets are properly safeguarded against wastage and loss;
Prepare necessary journal entries to adjust the duly investigated reconciling items supported with sufficient and appropriate documents in order to reflect the correct account balances; and
Instruct the Office of the Municipal Accountant to continue its effort to locate pertinent source documents to reduce the unidentified balances in the property ledger cards, if any, in order to render a reliable and accurate financial report.

19.2	Had the Municipality made a thorough inspection of the completed projects, the deficiencies noted could have been avoided. Moreover, if they meticulously prepared the POW of the above projects, overstatement of the cost of materials could have been prevented. Lower amount of POW leads to lesser Contract Price offered by the Bidders than the awarded contract amount, thereby saving of funds could be further used to finance other projects, programs and activities of the LGU.
19.3	We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Require those concerned officials during the inspection of the project - Extension of OTOP Store for Negosyo Center to submit explanation/justification regarding the deficiencies noted for evaluation of our COA-TAS;
Direct those concerned officials to meticulously prepare and review the POWs to ensure that only the required number of materials are included in the plan to avoid unnecessary costs, and to conduct thorough inspection of the projects to determine that this is in accordance with the approved Program of Works;
Require those concerned officials in the preparation of the POWs and inspection of the projects to refund the deficiencies noted; and
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to monitor the refund made by the persons liable.

3.9  We recommended to the Management that:
Instruct the Inventory Committee to exert more effort to complete the conduct of physical inventory of all PPE accounts;
A task force, composing of personnel from Accounting and GSO, be created to conduct the reconciliation of the affected accounts as soon as the physical count is complete;
The Accounting Office should prepare Journal Entry Vouchers to adjust reconciling items identified with sufficient and appropriate supporting documents;
The Municipal Accounting Office must exert extra effort to substantiate the unreconciled amount of P6,561,046.39 recorded in the Land account and make adjusting entries for infrastructure projects included in the Land account and record to its proper account.

7.4  We recommended that the management instruct the BAC and its Secretariat:
To  conduct pre-procurement conference for all procurement of Infrastructure with an ABC of above 5M;
To conduct pre-bid conference for all procurement with an ABC of 1M and more;
To require all winning bidders to submit construction safety and health program duly approved by the DOLE;
To submit a detailed TWG report on the evaluation on the bidder with the Lowest Calculated Bid (LCB) which was reviewed by the BAC;
To submit a post-qualification report; and
To strictly adhere with pertinent provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA 9184.
